## 🔑 API Keys Setup

### Required Keys

| Key | Required | Purpose | Get it from |
|-----|----------|---------|-------------|
| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | ✅ **Yes** | Primary AI engine | [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/apikey) |
| `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` | ⬜ Optional | Fallback AI engine | [OpenRouter](https://openrouter.ai/keys) |
| `IMAGE_API_KEY` | ⬜ Optional | Image generation | Depends on provider |

### Setting Keys by Platform

<details>
<summary><b>🪟 Windows</b></summary>

**Permanent (Recommended) — survives terminal restarts:**

```powershell
# PowerShell (run as Admin for system-wide)
[System.Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable("GEMINI_API_KEY", "your_key", "User")
[System.Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable("OPENROUTER_API_KEY", "your_key", "User")
[System.Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable("IMAGE_API_KEY", "your_key", "User")
```

```cmd
:: CMD
setx GEMINI_API_KEY "your_key"
setx OPENROUTER_API_KEY "your_key"
setx IMAGE_API_KEY "your_key"
```

> ⚠️ After `setx`, restart your terminal for changes to take effect.

**Temporary — current session only:**

```cmd
:: CMD
set GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key
```

```powershell
# PowerShell
$env:GEMINI_API_KEY="your_key"
```

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>🍎 macOS</b></summary>

**Permanent (add to your shell profile):**

```bash
# For zsh (default on macOS)
echo 'export GEMINI_API_KEY="your_key"' >> ~/.zshrc
echo 'export OPENROUTER_API_KEY="your_key"' >> ~/.zshrc
echo 'export IMAGE_API_KEY="your_key"' >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc
```

**Temporary:**

```bash
export GEMINI_API_KEY="your_key"
```

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>🐧 Linux</b></summary>

**Permanent:**

```bash
echo 'export GEMINI_API_KEY="your_key"' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'export OPENROUTER_API_KEY="your_key"' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'export IMAGE_API_KEY="your_key"' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
```

**Temporary:**

```bash
export GEMINI_API_KEY="your_key"
```

</details>

### Verify Keys

```bash
geminiviratpro
# Then type:
/chat hello
```

If you get a response → everything works ✅

