## 🔍 Troubleshooting

<details>
<summary><b>❌ "GEMINI_API_KEY not set"</b></summary>

Your API key isn't in the environment. Set it permanently (see [API Keys Setup](#-api-keys-setup)) and restart your terminal.

Verify with:
```bash
# Linux/macOS
echo $GEMINI_API_KEY

# Windows CMD
echo %GEMINI_API_KEY%

# PowerShell
echo $env:GEMINI_API_KEY
```
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>❌ "429 Too Many Requests"</b></summary>

You've hit the API rate limit. Wait 30–60 seconds and try again. Free-tier Gemini has a limit of ~15 requests/minute.
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>❌ "Python not found"</b></summary>

Ensure Python 3.8+ is installed and in your PATH:
```bash
python3 --version   # Linux/macOS
python --version     # Windows
```
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>❌ "ModuleNotFoundError: requests"</b></summary>

Install the requests library:
```bash
pip install requests
# or
pip3 install requests
```
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>❌ Agent stuck in a loop</b></summary>

The agent has a built-in limit of 10 iterations. If tasks aren't completing, try breaking them into smaller `/agent` commands.
</details>

